  "prompt": "How much time does HSBC take to provide offer letter?",
  "response": "The time it takes for HSBC, or any bank, to provide an offer letter can vary based on several factors, including the specific loan or account type, the completeness of your application, and the bank's internal processes. Typically, the process might take anywhere from a few days to a few weeks. \n\nFor home loans or personal loans, it often takes about 5 to 10 business days after the application is submitted, though it could take longer if additional documentation is required or if there are complexities in your application.\n\nFor the most accurate information, it's best to contact your local HSBC branch directly or check with their customer service for specific timelines related to your application.",
